caption: Really good place to dine

Changed our reservation twice on us.  Says online they have indoor dining (false advertising), walked all the way there for our reservation to find out they only offer outdoor seating in the freezing temperatures with small little heaters.  Also stated they are forcing vaccine on all staff. Yikes. Walked away and won’t be back.
Shrimp chips were fire
Great place, excellent food, incredible service. We love our local gem!

UNPROFESSIONAL and EXTREMLY RUDE servers. I ordered on Caviar and went to pick up my order. They asked for my name on 3 separate occasions when I was standing in the freezing cold 30 degree weather for at least 45 minutes. No explanation, no apologies, just said they would check on it and then ignored me and did not follow up with my order. Eventually I overheard them explaining to another customer who requested to dine in that they had an electrical problem. A Caviar employee who waited the same time as me also was asked on multiple occasions whose order he was waiting for until he was finally told they actually did not have the order in their system and he had to leave because it took too long and had been misled. At least 4 other customers were being treated in the same manner. I would have been fine if they had explained the issue however what was unacceptable was to be ignored and not receive an explanation that there were issues with my order, under extremely cold weather conditions.
Tableside heaters in the winter! Oysters are delicious and cocktails, though not very customizable, are delicious.
I have to wait my food like 1 hour and 20 min. Bad service
Great food and drink. A little over priced.
Amazing place. Highly recommend!
Really cool place and the only negative experience was our server (male) had this strange pretentiousness that rubbed us wrong. Other than he, would absolutely return. Excellent oysters.
Very unpleasant experience
Enjoyed our time there.

The cocktails at this restaurant are fantastic hands down. The food not so much! The crab dip was dry and completely burned straight through. The pasta was mediocre at best, sauce was too acidic and the giant olives were overwhelming. The service was lacking as well. We waited 50 minutes for our main course and about 30 for our appetizer. This was especially frustrating because the resturant locked down at 10pm and they knew we were pressed for time. I can not say I'll go back. In addition the tip defaulted to 25% and the service was not worth that much.

This place is solid. Great place to grab a cocktail or a meal. I have picked up to go drinks several times and they are always quality.  Sadly I did not make it there to eat before lockdown, but the food is great! I will definitely be excited to check it out whenever NYC restaurants can get back to full steam.  For now quality service, not a doctor, but seemingly solid process in checking temps, cleaning plenty of space between tables, and consistent mask use.
I was concerned about going to a buffet. This place has delicious food & so many things to choose from.  This was my 1st time & will definitely go back.
Fast and great service! and the staff are so nice!
Fun neighborhood place
Their food still tasted as great as a take away as when you sit down. Keeping the quality is key. Very good.
Good customer service is everything in food industry!!!
Good food and vibe overall, the service though... some really rude and condescending dudes coming off a little too strong.

Amazing service, fantastic food, lovely atmosphere. The back patio is a charming setup with enough greenery to make you forget you're in Brooklyn, livening up your lunch or dinner tenfold. The vast wine selection should cater to just about …
Good drinks and bites but not the friendliest place in the neighborhood from a staff perspective, let's leave it at that.

The cocktails are creative and strong, which is great. The food is also great, thought portions are small. For the price, I do hope for better service. The few times I've been, it's been pretty mediocre and the seating method is stressful.
Great cocktails! Dollar oysters are always a plus too!
kind staff and delicious food ❤️

Reopened after quarantine - awesome pick up!  So nice to see a local spot back after the city shut down for 2 months. I would walk by the dark windows every night during my nightly walks with my dog Ghost. So was thrilled to see them back in the neighborhood.  Here to praise their thoughtfulness to takeout, especially to take out oysters. Thank you!
Innovative and fresh. Crab fried rice and fish and eggplant were unexpected hits! Pricey, but worth it.

Great cocktails and an atmosphere that lends to conversation. I didn't go for nor indulged in the food, so hard to give it a full five stars, but with an oyster bar, I imagine it's something to enjoy.  Will definitely be back.

Came here on a Fri. night for drinks and snacks. LOVED IT. The service was excellent - our waitress specially picked our wine and recommended a ton of appetizers, which were all incredible. Even just the bread and butter were delicious! I will be back for a full-fledged dinner very soon. This is my new favorite spot in BK!
oysters were great, good beer on tap, the atmosphere was a bit loud for what i wanted but all good vibes

This is one of my favorite local spots. Love the menu and the bar. The staff is always chill, knowledgeable, and conversational. Also, you can beat the oyster happy hour!
Love everything about this place. Great drinks, atmosphere, staff. I always feel hip being here and the quality of drinks and food lives up to the vibe.

Never have my friends nor I been so disrespected at a bar. We were celebrating a friends bridal shower, the GENERAL MANAGER told us to be more quiet because we were too loud!! Did she get offended because we were debating about Jay Z not being the best rapper?! Or was it that we were the only Hispanics in the restaurant at the time, and the GM wanted to put us on time out since we were having a good time socializing and sharing stories amongst women of color celebrating, what was suppose to be one of our friends greatest moments. Thanks for ruining that for us GM of the Grand Army. Seems a bit racist, but let's not even talk about the 2 year old seated at the bar with his parents! That seems worse than have a group of women, visible having a good time at a BAR. how dare you tell us to quiet down at a BAR!!

Excellent Happy Hour food, excellent happy hour cocktails, and excellent happy hour service. We decided to cancel our previous reservations elsewhere & we stayed for dinner, as well. The place was hopping on a Friday night, but the service, the bartenders,  and the kitchen were all quite efficient. I was quite impressed. The seafood and the house oyster sauces were all excellent. I, WE (me & my wife), will definitely be back.

We stumbled upon this place walking around the neighborhood, and wow, we were so sorry we had not discovered it sooner. It has a relaxed and chic feel to it, we sat comfortably at the bar and enjoyed great conversation with the staff.  But it was the drinks that were the winners, they were crafted with care and the staff really offered unique selections. We asked for a gin drink, and the bartender made us a creation he had recently came up with. It. Was. Stellar.  Additionally, the food was amazing - surprisingly good seafood and oysters. This place is worth the time out of your day - stop reading this review and head on over there!
No comment, nothing to eat, nothing to drink. Change menu! There is only water and bread! It was ok, that is why 1 star.

Excellent from A to Z. The food is very original and delicious: I had octopus, country bread and butter, and and dessert. The staff is incredibly nice. The music is great (neo soul iirc). The place is busy but not too noisy. The bathroom is remarkably clean for such a busy place. If you're OK with eating under very dim lighting (which is a matter of taste), look no further than the Grand Army restaurant.
Great drinks and raw bar. Very small. Rather warm inside.
Awesome venue...The service, food and drinks was exceptional.

A gem right by Hoyt-Schemerhorn. Sunday cocktails and small plates were great. The Texas Rain is an excellent mezcal option. The crab devilled eggs and the roasted octopus were delicious. Not a bargain joint but worth it.

Best raw bar in the area. It comes a bowl filled with vials of sauces to try! I needed to order more oysters to try them all. But the king crab legs are the best. Great cocktails and wine list and your beer nerd friend will be able to find something to enjoy too. They also have the greatest toilet seat ever. I want to get my own. Make sure you look!
Good drinks and atmosphere. The steak tartar is amazing.
It may look like a cute neighborhood place but it’s a destination for drinks and raw bar. Beer, wine, and cocktail selections are all solid.
Outstanding cocktails and creative food menu. One of my favorites in this part of Brooklyn!

$1 oyster happy hour! They're good and the little bottles of sauces they serve it in is awesome! Of course they serve a good cocktail here as well and there is plenty of comfortable seating. There's no reason not to stop in here grab a drink and $1 oysters for happy hour! They even do it on weekends!!! It's a great spot to just chat with friends or grab that much needed drink after a long days work! Staff is super friendly as well and I never feel intimidated to order more than I want.
Fun spot for oysters and cocktails, with a great menu for sharing. The spot is small and busy so it gets loud, but not in a way modern NYC diners would be surprised by.
A great experience from individuals who care about what they're serving. Quality of ingredients was amazing. Next time I'm in Brooklyn will make sure to visit again.

A true Brooklyn staple. They have great drinks and the bartenders make some of the best cocktails in the area. There's also a great selection from their raw bar. It's a cozy and quaint neighborhood bar that I make sure to go to every time I'm in New York. Just a few blocks away from the subway as well.
Wait staff was great - even when we kept drinking and had to change waiters! They played Slum Village and I was happy - took me all the way back!

Seafood place with a range of unique cocktails. We had the Grand Army which consists of oysters, littleneck clams, shrimp and crab legs. All very fresh and tasty. The oysters are served with a pallete of sauces which weren't all that exciting - we stuck with the classics, and they were very good. Wine list is just ok, but you should go for the cocktails anyway. Will definitely visit again!

4.27.18 - The staff is really what makes this place great. We went for Oyster Happy Hour, which are a $1 each. Unfortunately, the ones for happy hour were small in nature, but still full of flavor and bright. The dipping sauces that come with the oysters include blue coconut, cucumber, shallot vinaigrette, and another yellow one.  There's usually a wait of about 15-20 minutes, but we got there just when a table opened up on a Friday night. The place can get loud and at times the service can get jammed up, but all in all it's a good options for Oyster Happy Hour.  The cocktails are balanced and full body or fruity. In the summer time it's great because the day is still bright, which lends itself to the charming interior.
Cocktails to talk about.

We’d walked past it a few times and it looked so charming.. and always busy! Luckily we were able to find places on a Tuesday night. Cozy setting inside and friendly service. While we didn’t have a chance to try the drinks, the Spring Cocktails sounded very intriguing. I ordered the Beef Tartare - delicious! (Wish it was a little bigger, but filling anyway) We shared Deviled Eggs as an appetizer and it was delightful. We’ll definitely be returning to try more!
GREAT COCKTAILS

It was OK

Delicious cocktails and friendly staff. A little expensive and a little crowded for my taste, but I'd definitely go again. I'm not into oysters, but if you are, they have $1 oyster deals. If you want table service, it's a good idea to male a reservation.

Wow! Amazing bar in downtown Bk, next to Atlantic-Dekalb hub. Great oysters, clams variety. Love the bread and butter thing. Lol All in all, if you happend to be in this area and are looking for a place to have a great time. This is it

Everything was wonderful. The food, the service, the ambiance. I enjoyed myself tremendously. Only thing was we sat next to a leaky window but other than that no complaints whatsoever.
Nice ambience. Food was  great!
Cute local bar. Awesome cocktails and selection. Also friendly hostess. Kinda hipster but not annoying.

Cocktails

Came here to visit Damon Boelte, host of the Speakeasy podcast, and owner of the Grand Army.  He showed up a few minutes after we did, and when I introduced my wife and I, he was very gracious.  He wasn't planning on staying at the bar, but made us a few cocktails, and hung out with us for a bit.  A real treat.  The cocktails and seafood are delicious, and when you order oysters it come with droppers that contain the most interesting flavors.

Honestly out of all my years in New York City as native New Yorker the most racist establishment I have ever been to. Before even placing my order I was practically escorted out and told I couldn't have a drink without much of an explanation heartbreaking to face such racism in New York City. Wouldn't recommend it if you're of color or have empathy for  victims of racism.
Great food and cocktails, intimate spot, feels like someone's living room. Good fun
Dollar oyster happy hour and delicious craft cocktails. What more do you want?

Come here for the dollar oysters. They have little sauces with droppers that are kitschy but  I'm personally better off with good old fashion lemon and cocktail sauce.  The craft cocktails are always changing and super yummy. About the average price range for NYC and what you'd expect to pay for a drink shaken with egg whites.  The staff has always been helpful and friendly in my experience. I'd recommend it as a date spot or a girl's night jump off.
good for a try
